-----Original Message-----
From: Dave Dixon
Subject: Re: [VB] Oil leak at Oil Pump cover


Hi Ray,

This pump is a VW heavy duty pump made by Empi with a cover that has a
screw on filter attachment. There is a single circular slot in the pump
body that faces the pump cover. I put an O-ring that came with the pump
of equal size into this slot then bolted the cover on. I think maybe I
should have also included a thin paper gasket, hence the source of the
leak.

Are you saying that the O-ring should not have been used here? These
engines are so cool. If they aren't put together right, they will
usually let you know.

Dave
